See Memory_Models.jpg image for flow chart.

Flat Model
	Can access any address directly

Segmented Model
	You use a Segment Selector along with an Offset to find out the location of the address

Real-Address Mode Model
	Similar to Segmented Model (Uses rare cases)



32Bit Linux uses:
	Protected Mode
	Flat Memory Model
	4GB Addressable space => 2^32
	Memory Protection
	Privilege Levels of Code
	Segmented Registers point to degmented Descripters (GDT, LDT, IDT (Global, Local, Interrupt) Descripter Tables)
